OL,4,CUK airports to fight 'silent killer'
OL,6,FBut campaigners insist more must still
OL,7,Fbe done to beat this silent killer.
OL,9,FHudson Foley was travelling in Ecuador
OL,10,Fwhen the toxic gas - which cannot be
OL,11,Fseen or smelled - took his life.
OL,13,FHis mother, Cathy, said she only found
OL,14,Fout that her son had been poisoned
OL,15,Fafter a blood test came back eight
OL,16,Fweeks later.
OL,18,FShe said his death was made more
OL,19,Ftragic by the fact that it was
OL,20,F"completely preventable" had he had an
OL,21,Falarm with him.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/9
