OL,6,F"We want people to be aware that
OL,7,Fregulations around the world are
OL,8,Fdifferent; there are no international
OL,9,Fstandards. Almost 30,000 people die of
OL,10,Fcarbon monoxide every year around the
OL,11,Fworld."
OL,13,FShe insists more still needs to be
OL,14,Fdone to beat this silent killer.
OL,16,F"Ultimately, it is the traveller's
OL,17,Fresponsibility as well, and the travel
OL,18,Findustry, so we all have to work
OL,19,Ftogether," she said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/9
